+## [1.0.5.post2+edorp] — 2026-07-13
+
+### Fixes
+
+- Snapshot active network services before `airmon-ng check kill` and restart
+  only those services when `--restore` is requested.
+- Refuse `--kill --restore` when the active-service snapshot fails, handle
+  SIGTERM/SIGHUP through orderly cleanup, and continue after individual service
+  restart errors.
+- Restore services even when monitor-mode setup fails, and avoid repeated
+  conflict-kill calls during interface recovery.
+- Use the current recovered interface name when returning the radio to managed
+  mode after a driver reprobe; verify the result and fall back to direct
+  `iw` conversion when `airmon-ng stop` fails.
+- Reject missing, empty, directory, or unreadable explicit `--dict` paths
+  before dependency checks or privileged radio setup.
+
+## [1.0.5.post1+edorp] — 2026-07-13
+
+Downstream reliability build for the EDORP installer bundle.
+
+### Fixes
+
+- Recover the same wireless adapter after a driver reprobe, update renamed
+  monitor interfaces, and fail explicitly instead of reusing a stale name.
+- Capture and display bounded `airodump-ng` output when capture startup fails;
+  use the newest CAP file after a restart.
+- Detect Reaver/Bully fatal signals and disable further WPS attacks for the
+  session (including `--infinite` rescans) while allowing PMKID and handshake
+  capture to continue.
+- Disable Wash after its first fatal crash instead of spawning it repeatedly.
+- Route algorithmic PIN attempts through the selected WPS backend, correct
+  Bully's ignore-lock flag to `-L`, and enforce one overall WPS timeout.
+- Sanitize terminal control sequences and Rich markup in external-tool output
+  and recovered keys without modifying the raw key saved to the results store.
+
